==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sebacic
<hw>Se*bac"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>sebum</ets>
tallow: cf. F. <ets>s⟦eacute⟧bacique</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to fat; derived from, or resembling, fat;
specifically, designating an acid (formerly called also
<altname>sebic</altname>, and <altname>pyroleic</altname>, acid),
obtained by the distillation or saponification of certain oils (as
castor oil) as a white crystalline substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sebat</ent>⟦br⟧
